---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Kirk Brooks. An engineer and founder who finds the real problem and builds the fix."
>
  <section class="page-head">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="lead">I find the real problem and build the fix.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I am a mechanical engineer with aerospace roots who became a software
      builder. The constant across everything I do is the same move: find a real
      problem people are working around badly, make the durable call, and ship
      the thing that solves it.
    </p>
    <p>
      I am domain-agnostic on purpose. The problem matters to me more than the
      field, whether that is version control for CAD, enterprise training that
      has to run on a disconnected network, or a travel app that plans around
      festivals. Still, one thread does run through all of it. I love building
      things that help other builders, the tools and platforms that make it
      easier for people to design, make, and ship real work. I am happiest
      embedded in a hard problem and owning what gets built.
    </p>
    <p>
      My main language is C# and .NET, from years of building and running Febris.
      I reach for whatever the problem actually needs, which is how I have also
      shipped Rust backends, a Python and OpenCASCADE geometry pipeline, and
      React front ends. From 2019 to 2023 I ran my own homelab, a Dell PowerEdge
      R720xd with a few enterprise SSDs and around 100 GB of RAM, for running and
      testing software and standing up my own builds the moment I wanted to try
      them. The mechanical-engineering background did not
      go anywhere. It just found a new place to be useful.
    </p>
    <p>
      For the past two years I have lived and worked on the road, from an
      off-grid-capable Airstream with a redundant electrical system and
      satellite internet, an office I engineered before I ever called remote a
      preference. Living this way surfaces real problems: finding the festival
      worth the detour, navigating unfamiliar roads, the stretches where
      connectivity is a fight, all while parked somewhere genuinely beautiful.
      Festurah grew out of one of those. When a project calls for it, I can point
      the whole rig at a customer's site and be there in person for a month.
      Remote is not a perk I am asking for, it is how I already work.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="about-block">
    <h2>Background</h2>
    <dl class="spec-list">
      <div class="spec-row">
        <dt class="spec-key">2012 to 2016</dt>
        <dd class="spec-val">
          <strong>Intern to Lead Project Engineer, ES3.</strong> Aerospace
          research and development. Led an additive-manufacturing cold-spray
          R&amp;D program from concept through validation, authored overhaul
          manuals for the C-5 and F/A-18 airframes, and designed mechanical test
          fixtures and nondestructive failure-detection methods.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <dt class="spec-key">Education</dt>
        <dd class="spec-val">
          <strong>B.S.E. in Mechanical Engineering</strong>, Mercer University.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <dt class="spec-key">Clearance</dt>
        <dd class="spec-val">
          U.S. citizen. Secret clearance eligibility via a favorably adjudicated
          Tier 3 investigation, inactive since 2016.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="about-block">
    <h2>Skills</h2>
    <dl class="spec-list">
      <div class="spec-row">
        <dt class="spec-key">Languages</dt>
        <dd class="spec-val">
          C# and .NET (primary), Python, TypeScript and JavaScript, and Rust.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <dt class="spec-key">Systems and web</dt>
        <dd class="spec-val">
          React, Axum, PostgreSQL, Docker, Kubernetes, Azure, distributed
          systems, Git and Git LFS.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-row">
        <dt class="spec-key">Engineering</dt>
        <dd class="spec-val">
          CAD in SolidWorks, Creo, and AutoCAD, GD&amp;T, tolerance stack-ups,
          bills of materials, DFM and DFA, FEA, additive manufacturing, and CNC.
          Plus enterprise XR and AR systems.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="about-block">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Based in {site.location}. {site.availability}</p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      {site.email && <a class="btn btn-primary" href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>Email me</a>}
      {site.socials.linkedin && <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={site.socials.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>}
      {site.socials.github && <a class="btn btn-ghost" href={site.socials.github} target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>}
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
